ずっと僕の夢だったこの国を入ることを。きょうがいなっきゃこの夢は無理かも、ありがとうきょう！あの日本の初日はきっと忘れない、全てが新しく見えた、すべてが綺麗に見えた。
。
ナイーブ、ナイーブだった。ここの生活とインドネシア🇮🇩の生活は全く違いだ。何もかもが違いすぎて、僕がちっぽけになった気がした。でも僕は信じるから、僕はこんなもんじゃないってことを変わるっと決めた。
。
どうすれば変わる？！何をするのかわからない僕が富士山を登った、一人で。初めてにこの人生で山を登った、あのいつもの学生のカバンがきゅにキャリアーになったwww.

きょうの半分と再会してよかた！リファルドーは変わった、でもまだあの頃のままのネガだ。これからの興はきっと前よりいい！

.
It seems like I’m cursed to befriend so close with every aldo around me HAHA. I can’t thank you enough, escorting you to this point might be my best token of appreciation for you. Upon landing there, you will then proceed your journey of the new unexplored land, where I believe you will find tons of eye-opening things. We’re still here looking up to the same sky, as the sky had already connected us before social media connects us. I believe the place you’re about to explore will be the place where you can change, or even change. .
.
This sounds unbelievable but you were the very first person that I’ve witnessed, that is able to persevere for what you really strive for literally round-the-clock. And ya, I extremely believe that you’ve got what it takes to learn everything that you want to learn. If I happen to find someone that is able to show that level of persistence as yours one day when I have my own VC —I wonder when would it be—, that virtue would definitely be a golden-ticket for that someone to get my investment HAHA. I do concede my defeat on this one, I should learn from you more. And you should learn more about getting enough sleep from your surroundings mate, seriously.
.
But still, among every random discussion that we’ve done, the best one was when you asked “Bim, nanti tulisanlu di buku itu bakal dijadiin materi semua?“. It was as if you never question whether I will make it or not, you asked it as if it was obvious for me HAHA you’re so naive I like it. Though I lost my book in Hangzhou, China last month, I still recorded every piece of it and I hope all these memories will stay in form until the time comes, when I need to recall all of it and reunite all the puzzles, creating impact on Indonesia.
.
If there’s one thing that I can change from this world, I would like to change Indonesia to the state that satisfy you enough which then make you willing to level-up this country alongside with me. Though ya I can’t change Indonesia if I write too much caption HAHA. Let me go back to work ya. Let’s hope that by the time you’re about to register your PR in Aussie, this country will be ready enough to welcome you. .
.

One question that I frequently received was "bim, kok lu tinggal di asrama?". Upon hearing this, I would always then giggled and answered "murah".
.
It ended so fast ya @aldopaian ! I still remember clearly the moment my family and I prayed in this dorm at the very first day of my living here. It was just like yesterday when aldo brought his air-con to this room, plugged it in, and the electricity when outaged. duh.
.
We sang together, talked to each other, and learnt from each other a lot. We even did deep-sharing (didn't we? HAHA) at the last quarter of this dorm-life. We often ended our day with a "go-food kuy" --which is not a verb actually--, then this two-fanned room will always be our shelter where we could just be "us".
.
This US$22-monthly-priced dorm made me learn things that I believe can't be acquired anywhere. That modesty is beautiful, that people do change, and that living in solitude is tough.
.
I can't say that you were a great roommate, nor I don't think you would consider me as a great roommate too. But you were definitely my best roommate as you were the first roommate I've ever had. Though we're now splitted apart, I believe we still can develop each other through our own way. ThanKyou do! (kita blm cover lagu bareng neh btw)
.
It's sad how I can't use the "bisa buat tinggal di asrama X hari neh" joke again. HA!
Thanks to @aldi_sutedja who captured the change through his view. .
2017年6月3日

Gw mau ngejawab semua orang yang suka nanya ke gw nih, pertanyaannya kurang lebih kaya gini, ini hampir gw denger tiap hari dulu pas maba.
"bim, kok lu bacot/ banyak omong/ sombong/ jumawa?" .
Hehehe sorry nih sebelumnya tiap gw bacot itu gw hampir ngga pernah ada tujuan meremehkan ato apa2 kok. Tapi karena gw percaya bahwa ucapan adalah doa, gw suka deh ngomong2 seenaknya sampe gw dicap sombong. Coba deh itu buka foto ig yang paling pertama gw post. Udah baca bacotannya?
.
Sekarang udah 1/2 tahun sejak gw post itu, dan gw berhasil nyatain bacotan itu. Singkat cerita, di hari ini gw untuk pertama kalinya diundang untuk jadi "pembicara" di acara Entrepreneurshipnya FHUI. Seruu, ngga gitu rame tapi gw rasa gw berhasil engage semua partisipannya untuk peduli sama apa yg gw bawain. Yoi kan bisa pas 1/2 tahun gitu timingnya, gw rasa gw ngga akan bisa diri di situ kalo gw ngga bacot itu 1/2 tahun yang lalu.
.
Eh ini bukan berarti maksud gw bacot aja terus- terusan, kagak. Jadi gini nih ya kalo gw jelasin thought process gw. Lu bacot dulu tuh, nah kan abis bacot alam bawah sadarlu bakal ngerecord bacotan itu, disini lu jadi udah tau mau jalan kemana. Di saat yang sama bakal ada nih manusia2 yang ngatain lu atau nge-aminin bacotanlu. .
Lanjut lanjut, untuk yang ngatain lu, ini ada quote kerennya nih "When people underestimate you don't be down, stand up and let them know that they're wrong.“ Untuk yang nge-amininlu, anggep itu sebagai temen2lu yang berani naro kepercayaan mereka untuk masang ekspektasi dari lu. Jadi jadi intinya yang niatny mau nurunin mentallu itu bisa lu jadiin sebagai leverage buat lu nyatain apa yang udah lu bacotin, apalagi yang aminin lu kan keren. Terus ya, kerja lah. Kalo ngga kerja mana bisa dinyatain bacotannya.
.
Jadi terus bersyukur yaa kalo ada yang ngatain lu atau aminin apa yang lu bacotin, karena mereka semua udah nambahin "why" buat lu untuk lu ngelakuin sesuatu. Terlebih tentang ekspektasi, gw agak ngga suka ngehianatin ekspektasi orang jadi makin banyak yang support, gw makin tergerak. Kayanya rata2 semua manusia gitu ngga sih? [EH LANJUT KE KOMEN YA, KEPANJANGAN NIH]
.
